The paper presents a novel machine-learning approach for estimating individual dose-response curves, which involves developing performance metrics, model selection criteria, and model architectures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the practical relevance of the approach for fields such as healthcare, economics, and public policy, indicating that it may also belong to the Computational Economics (cs.CE), Cybernetics (cs.CY), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
